National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location:
GRAND HAVEN, MI
Accident Number:
CHI82DA229
Date & Time:
07/01/1982, 1015 EDT 
Registration:
N211SB
Aircraft:
CLANCY SKYBABY
Aircraft Damage:
Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries:
1 Minor
Flight Conducted Under:
Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
Analysis 
DURING THE PILOTS FOURTH TAKEOFF ROLL OF THE DAY THE RIGHT WING BEGAN 
TO DROP AND THE AIRCRAFT DRIFTED OFF THE RUNWAY. POWER WAS REDUCED 
AND BRAKES APPLIED BUT THE AIRCRAFT OVERTURNED AFTER ENCOUNTERING A 
SOFT SODDED AREA. AFTER THE ACCIDENT IT WAS NOTED THAT THE 1/4 INCH BOLT 
WAS MISSING FROM THE REAR MOUNTING OF THE RIGHT LANDING GEAR RADIUS 
ARM. THE UNDAMAGED BOLT WAS FOUND ABOUT 100 FT EAST OF THE POINT 
WHERE THE PILOT STATED THAT THE AIRCRAFT STARTED TO DRIFT. 
Probable Cause and Findings
The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be:
